            <p>I researched how much data could be sent over a single NFC transfer and found that the limit is quite low, the max being around 8kB.</p>

            <p>With this information I decided to look into other ways in which the user would be able to get their receipt. One idea i came up with was for the merchant to send the receipt information to our database and use NFC to send the receipt ID over to the customer. Once the customer has an internet connection, they use that ID to pull the receipt information from our database.</p>

            <p>Looked into POS.</p>

            <p>Looked into if a customer would be able to return goods if they didn't have a physical receipt but if they had the information it contained.</p>
