            <h4 class="text-secondary">Cross Platform</h4>
            <p>After the meeting with the lecturers, Dermot suggested that we look into a cross-platform framework to allow the app to be accessible on both Android and iOS. Nick and I thought about this idea but decided on making it native, starting with Android for the initial release and in the future aim towards iOS.</p>

            <h4 class="text-secondary">Native</h4>
            <p>The benefits of native is that the app will be more secure, faster and have more control over certain features.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Security is important in this app as the items a user buys or even the just the brand can be personal. It is also important not to allow outsiders to gain a duplicate of the receipt as false returns would be an issue.</li>
                <li>Speed and accessibility is important as when out and about, a user doesn't want to spend extra time loading receipts or creating longer queues in shops.</li>
                <li>Control over NFC is important in the transfer of data between merchant and customer. In the past apple had rules on the use of NFC access, with this information we decided that the control over NFC could be tricky and is best we have the best control possible over it.</li>
